    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-11-19T02:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-11-19T02:00:00-05:00" n="32"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d32">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">783.003/126: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Egypt</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Childs</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Cairo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-11-19T09:00:00+02:00"
                            >November 19, 1936—9 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 9:10 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>63. Approval of the Egyptian Parliament of the Anglo-Egyptian treaty<note n="36"
                        xml:id="d32fn36">Signed at London, August 26, 1936; for text, see British
                        Treaty Series No. 6 (1937): <hi rend="italic">Treaty of Alliance,
                        etc</hi>.</note> was completed last night. The High Commissioner<note n="37"
                        xml:id="d32fn37">Sir Miles Lampson.</note> informed me yesterday both he and
                    the Egyptian Government desired to convene the Capitulations Conference as soon
                    as possible after ratification by the British Government and suggested January
                    15th as a possible date. The place is also still undetermined.</p>
                <p>On the basis of other information I am doubtful if as early a date as January may
                    be possible.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Childs</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
